title._content: Australasian swimming team, winners of the freestyle relay, Olympic Games, Stockholm, 1912.

description._content: Title supplied by cataloguer.; Condition: good.; Inscriptions: "Olympiska spelens i stockholm 1912 officiella Brefkort", "Granbergs Konstingustri-Aktiebolags Forlag, Stockholm", "Australasia's team, 1st prize in team race 800 m." -- printed on reverse with coat of arms.; Also available in an electronic version via the Internet at: u nla.gov.au/nla.pic-an21171586; Exhibited: "Seabaths", National Library of Australia Visitors Centre, February - August 2005. Official postcard with photograph of the Australasian relay team who won the 4x200 metres freestyle relay. Swimmers were Malcolm Champion (N.Z.), Harold Hardwick (Aus.), Cecil Healy (Aus.), and Leslie Boardman (Aus.). Persistent URL nla.gov.au/nla.pic-an21171586
